# Built corpus binaries are dev-tooling; rebuild via `make` (requires
# x86_64-w64-mingw32-gcc).  We do NOT check them into the repo because
# (a) they're 100-200 KB each x 10 = ~1.5 MB of binary churn per
# toolchain bump, and (b) build-machine determinism on PE timestamps is
# tricky.  CI/devs run `make all` to regenerate.
*.exe
*.o
*.obj
# Keep .gitignore + Makefile + sources.
!.gitignore
!Makefile
!*.c
!*.h
